result.name: Tseung Kwan O Plaza

reviews.text: Has everything you need incl movie theatre & air con, which is good during summer!

Worth visiting the small wet market for fresh fish, fruit and veg, frozen food, small supermarket and various other little shops. 

Prices are a little cheaper than Saikung and Hang Hau wet markets and the food quality the same. 

Upstairs in the main shopping mall expect to find all the usual brands plus restaurants. TKO Plaza connects to Popcorn 1&2 malls. 

TKO Plaza has changed the free parking mechanism in that only receipts proving credit card payment will be accepted.
Quite nice, big and different shops. Recommended for tourists.
I love the parking place, with enough spaces to each car, and reasonable daily parking, just $75 for 12hours, good?

A big mall for shopping and dining with a cinema and many popular outlets and brand names. Lots of public areas and parks nearby and it shares other malls under one roof by joined walkways and bridges. Great for when it rains and plenty of choices to shop and eat.

Right on top of mtr so easy to get to and conveniently located from hustle and bustle of HK Island.
